laboratory_examinations.findings: Short segment of bowel wall thickening with pericolonic fat stranding and diverticulosis at the level of the proximal transverse colon. Equivocal evidence for tiny extraluminal gas adjacent to the area of inflammation. Additional areas of diverticulosis noted along the cecum and sigmoid colon.
Result indicates presence of Corynebacterium species, with a reference range lower limit of 0.0 and upper limit of 149.0.
